The Konshisha Local Government traditional council has banished two men from the local government for killing two girls through witchcraft. The two girls, Mbasen and Mbawuese, were mysteriously   drown in River Agberagba last week. Agberagba is the headquarters of Konshisha local Government area in Benue north east senatorial zone. However, after the bodies of the two girls from recovered from the river youths mobilised and arrested two suspects. The suspects, Mbashinya Abata and Terna Ikyondu, confessed to killing the two girls inside the river. The suspects were almost killed by mob action but the Divisional Police Officer (DPO) Fidelis Jombo led a team of police to rescue them. However, the traditional ruler of Konsshisha (Ter Ikyor) Chief Jam Gbiinde and his council in chief intervened in the matter and banished the two suspects from the community. . Chief Gbinde said such habit will not be welcomed in his community and warned his subjects against witchcraft. 